ements of university students to romantic love triangle erotica to a story that examines teacher-student love and the norms of sex and age, Cui centers queer sexuality as a core part of human experience. Richly imaginative and vividly written, Platinum Bible of the Public Toilet portrays the emergence of queer cultures in postsocialist China while foregrounding the commitments to one’s erotic and passionate attractions even as they lead to cultural transgressions. This volume includes a preface by and an interview with the author.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChinese fictiony20th centuryvTranslations into English. 0aChinese fictiony21st centuryvTranslations into English. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aLiu, Petrus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiu, Petrus, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRofel, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRofel, Lisa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRojas, Carlos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311135689140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478059066?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478059066423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478059066/original  a978-3-11-135689-1  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles